news.title: Real estate, NBFCs lead salary growth in 2026: Aon study
news.para: Salaries in India are projected to rise by nine percent in 2026, led by robust growth in real estate and NBFCs. These sectors are experiencing high talent demand due to government spending and market upcycles. Overall attrition has declined, indicating improved employee stability and retention efforts across organized sectors.

news.title: Private equity investors drive $3.9 billion into Indian real estate in Jan-Sept 2025
news.para: Indian real estate attracted $1.5 billion in private equity during Q3 2025, a 32% dip year-on-year, yet year-to-date inflows remain robust. The office sector led with 39% of investments, closely followed by data centers. Foreign investors are driving over 65% of year-to-date funding, signaling strong confidence in India's long-term real estate prospects.

news.title: About ₹90,000 crore investment to double India's third party data centre capacity by FY28: ICRA
news.para: India's data centre capacity is set to double to 2,400-2,500 MW by FY28, fueled by a massive ₹90,000 crore investment pipeline. Mumbai leads the charge, contributing over half of the current operational capacity.  A proposed 20-year tax exemption policy could significantly boost this growth, making India a stronger player in the global data centre market.

news.title: Cement companies to add 41-43 million MTPA capacity in FY26: ICRA
news.para: A recent GST cut on cement is set to slash rural housing construction costs by up to 1%, making homes more affordable. Cement companies anticipate a 3-5% rise in realization and a 12-18% boost in operating profit per ton for FY26, fueled by robust demand and stable input prices. Green energy adoption is also on the rise.

news.title: GCCs to incrementally lease 50-55 million sq ft during FY26-FY27: ICRA
news.para: Global capability centers are projected to lease 50-55 million sq ft of office space in India's top six cities by FY26-FY27, contributing significantly to overall demand. With over 1,700 GCCs currently, their numbers are expected to surpass 2,500 by 2030, driving substantial revenue and workforce growth.

news.title: About 6.5 lakh illegal properties around Bengaluru to get e-khata under e-swathu drive
news.para: Bengaluru's e-Swathu initiative will provide e-khatas to 6.5 lakh unauthorized properties in gram panchayats, bringing them into the tax net. This aims to regularize over 95 lakh illegal properties statewide, enabling property owners to complete transactions and avail bank loans. The program is expected to significantly boost property tax collections for gram panchayats.

news.title: DDA to hold weekly camps for housing conversion cases in Delhi
news.para: The Delhi Development Authority (DDA) is launching weekly special camps every Thursday to expedite housing conversion cases from leasehold to freehold. These camps, initially held at Vikas Sadan, aim to provide on-the-spot resolution for allottees' queries and document submission, simplifying the process and addressing resident complaints about ownership rights.

news.title: FIR filed against Ocean Seven Buildtech for ₹217 crore housing fraud
news.para: Delhi Police's EOW has filed an FIR against Ocean Seven Buildtech and its MD for allegedly cheating homebuyers and diverting Rs 217 crore from the incomplete Expressway Towers project. Buyers accuse the developer of misrepresentation and fraudulent resale of units, while the developer denies fraud, citing pandemic and NGT restrictions for delays.

news.title: Duroply eyes 15–18% growth in FY26; to ramp West & South markets
news.para: Duroply Industries anticipates 15-18% year-on-year growth, confident in achieving its 15% revenue target for FY25. The company leverages an asset-light model and contract manufacturing, expecting policy changes and improving macroeconomics to drive sector growth. Duroply is also investing in brand building and exploring AI for quality control.

news.title: Century Plyboards lines up ₹150-crore plywood capex in Punjab; eyes zero debt by FY27
news.para: Century Plyboards anticipates robust growth, maintaining its full-year guidance despite a soft market. The company reported a strong first quarter and is expanding capacity with new particle board and plywood plants.  Focusing on PVC boards and exports, Century Ply aims for significant revenue growth and a zero-debt position by FY27, championing sustainable agro-forestry practices.

news.title: JPMorgan seeks to attract staff with $3 billion skyscraper in New York
news.para: JPMorgan Chase has unveiled its new 60-story headquarters in Manhattan.  It is designed to attract and retain talent, serving as a model for future global offices. The bank has also upgraded workstations in several international locations and plans further enhancements.

news.title: Awfis looks to grow 30% in FY26, eyes 40% non-core business revenue: Amit Ramani
news.para: Awfis Space Solutions targets robust FY26 growth with a 30% revenue increase to ₹1,600 crore, adding 40,000 coworking seats. The company maintains strong EBITDA margins and RoCE, while diversifying revenue through ancillary services.  Awfis emphasizes its medium-sized center strategy and network density for risk mitigation.

news.title: Nimbus projects adds ₹1,100 crore development potential with favourable order from UP government
news.para: UPIDA has directed the Yamuna authority to recalculate land allotment for Nimbus Projects, granting an additional 1.1 million sq ft with a Rs 1,100 crore development potential. This order, following a revision petition, resolves a long-pending issue for the IITL-Nimbus project. The company also reported a rise in sales bookings and collections for Q2 FY 2025-26.

news.title: Ahmedabad’s urban body tells developers to maintain percolation wells for BU permit
news.para: Ahmedabad Urban Development Authority (Auda) now mandates developers to maintain percolation wells for building use permission, requiring notarized affidavits for operational status. This move reinforces existing regulations, as Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation also collects deposits for well maintenance, aiming to combat waterlogging and ensure groundwater recharge.

news.title: Telangana to unlock more land auction after ₹3,135-crore Raidurg record
news.para: Following a record-breaking land sale, Telangana is auctioning another prime parcel in Hyderabad's Knowledge City for an estimated Rs 200 crore. This move signals the state's strategy to monetize high-value urban land amid strong investor demand in the city's western corridor, known for its IT and financial ecosystem.

news.title: Marathon Nextgen Realty & Adani Realty to jointly develop commercial project in Mumbai
news.para: Marathon Nextgen Realty has partnered with Adani Realty to develop Monte South Commercial, a 1.2 million sq ft office and retail project in Byculla, Mumbai. This development, with an estimated gross value of ₹3,400 crore, is part of the larger Monte South campus, which also includes four residential towers.

news.title: Institutional-grade malls now form 30–35% of India’s 650 operational malls: Report
news.para: India's retail malls are becoming more professional. Many now meet high standards, attracting significant investment. Developers are building larger, experience-focused malls. This trend is expanding beyond major cities into smaller hubs. New GST reforms are expected to boost transparency and investor confidence, further fueling growth in the organized retail sector.

news.title: Private equity inflows in Indian real estate fall 15% in H1 FY26: Report
news.para: Private equity real estate investments in India moderated in H1 FY26, with inflows down 15% year-on-year to USD 2.2 billion. While deal concentration eased, retail, mixed-use, and office sectors saw increased traction, and foreign capital rebounded, contributing 73% of inflows.

news.title: Indian retail REITs may touch ₹80,000 crore by 2030: Report
news.para: Retail REITs are projected to become a significant ₹60,000–80,000 crore opportunity by 2030, potentially forming 30-40% of India's total REIT market. This growth is driven by maturing Grade A malls, rising urban incomes, and steady consumption, with tier-II cities emerging as key growth hotspots for new retail developments.

news.title: Redevelopment projects to unlock over 44,000 new homes in Mumbai: Report
news.para: Mumbai's society redevelopment projects are set to deliver 44,277 new homes by 2030, valued at ₹1,305 billion. Over 910 housing societies have signed development agreements since 2020, unlocking significant land potential. Western Suburbs lead this transformation, with Borivali, Andheri, and Bandra emerging as key redevelopment hotspots.
